Languages:
  - Rust (edition 2021)

Frameworks / Libraries:
  - eframe 0.27    — GUI framework (egui native wrapper)
  - egui 0.27      — Immediate-mode GUI
  - enigo 0.6      — Cross-platform keyboard/mouse input simulation (Wayland feature enabled)
  - rdev 0.5       — Global keyboard/mouse event listener (Windows/macOS fallback)
  - evdev 0.13     — Linux input event device listener (non-exclusive, works on X11 + Wayland)
  - serde 1        — Serialization/deserialization (with derive)
  - toml 0.8       — TOML config file format
  - dirs 5         — OS config directory resolution
  - log 0.4        — Logging facade
  - env_logger 0.11 — Environment-based logger (RUST_LOG)

Architecture:
  - Clean architecture with 3 layers:
    - domain/    — Entities & port traits (no external dependencies)
    - app/       — Application state & config
    - infra/     — Infrastructure: UI, input, config persistence, listener
  - Trait-based abstraction for input engine (InputEnginePort)
  - Trait-based abstraction for config persistence (ConfigPort)
  - Arc<AppState> shared between UI thread and listener thread
  - AtomicBool for active flag (lock-free cross-thread signaling)
  - AtomicBool (static SPRAYING) for AR/SMG spray loop control
  - Mutex<AppConfig> for shared config access
  - Mode dispatch: handle_lclick_press/release routes to mode-specific logic
  - Platform-conditional listener: evdev on Linux, Win32 Raw Input API (RegisterRawInputDevices + WM_INPUT, HWND_MESSAGE pump) on Windows, rdev on macOS

Modes:
  - Sniper: 4-step sequence (RClick → LClick → RClick → Switch), trigger on L-Click
  - AR/SMG: hold-to-spray loop with optional recoil pull, trigger on L-Click press/release
  - Shotgun: 2-step sequence (LClick → Switch), trigger on L-Click

UI Design:
  - Dark theme (egui::Visuals::dark)
  - Fixed window 300x420, non-resizable
  - Vertical layout: label on top, full-width slider below
  - Bahasa Indonesia labels throughout

Build / Tooling:
  - Cargo (Rust package manager)
  - Platform-conditional deps: evdev only on Linux
